body:
@robpike, thanks for your quick reply.
The code you write in https://play.golang.org/p/VhCbdtJzwz looks great. As you mentioned, there is no excellent implementation reason to have Set as builtin type.
I understand and accept, Golang wants to keep simple principle. On the other hand, I still think the code will be more graceful if we have Set builtin type but not via map. I hope someday someone could give an excellent reason. I will close the proposal anyway!
